transcript.text: Welcome to on print shop in store personalization we will see sidebar management.

In sidebar management we will see why sidebar how to activate deactivate sidebar how to manage sidebar and sidebar widget Why sidebar The sidebar of your site is a great place to add information and anything else you want your visitor to have easy access to no matter what page they land on.
How to activate or deactivate a sidebar?
So when we go to the storefront on the home page over here, you can see there is a no sidebar on left hand side or right hand side.
Now how to activate the sidebar or deactivate the sidebar?
Let's see in the admin panel, we'll need to go to store personalization sidebar management.
From here, you can activate or deactivate a sidebar.
First you can see the default 1.
So this default 1 is like say if you have not activated any sidebar on any pages displayed over here, then this default sidebar will be displayed on that page.
Now let's talk about the home page.
We have seen home page there is no sidebar.
So we want to activate a sidebar on the home page.
So to activate a sidebar on a home page, you will do first decide which sidebar you want to activate left sidebar or right sidebar.
Then suppose you want to activate a left sidebar.

Then over here under the drop down you select yes and click on save button in top right hand corner and now on the storefront you can see the left sidebar is activated with the widgets of product, category and languages.
Now suppose I want to activate the right side sidebar.
Then in the right sidebar I'll select yes, click on save and go to storefront Refresh and the right sidebar is also activated.
Now you can see the widget on right sidebar is Customer Login and Deal of the week.
Now I don't want this widget deal of the week and also want to deactivate the left sidebar.
Then I'll go to sidebar management from here, left sidebar, I'll select no.
And to remove the widget deal of the week, I'll click on this pencil like button, The edit button, I'll click on that.
I'll select deal of the week over here.
So whichever widget you select over here, they will not be displayed on the page.
They will be hidden.
So I'll click save and now when I refresh the page, see you can see the deal of the week has been removed from here and the left sidebar and select no.
Click on save and the left sider will be removed.
You can see the left sidebar has been removed.
So this is how you can activate or deactivate a sidebar or activate or deactivate a widget of a sidebar.
Now to manage a widget of a sidebar, you go to sidebar management sidebar widget.
From here you cannot add a new widget or you cannot remove or delete a widget.
You can only edit a widget.

So to edit a widget just click on action button, click on edit and from here you can only edit the title, position of the widget, display of the widget like say always before login, after login or only user account pages, the short order of the widget and status active or inactive and the position of the widget left and right.
But you cannot delete or add a new widget.
So this is how you can manage a sidebar and a sidebar widget.
Thank you for watching this video.

What exactly is Online Printing System?
Online Printing System is a prepress process that bridges the gap
between online digital content and commercial print production. The
process allows a print house, a client or a graphic designer to create,
edit, and approve computer-based online templates during the prepress
phase. This process increasingly calls for a Portable Document Format
(PDF) workflow environment with output provided by digital printing.
